{
  "name": "Shortsword, Crusading",
  "type": "weapon",
  "img": "systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/yellow_16.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This is a sentient lawful good&nbsp;<em>+1 shortsword</em>&nbsp;(Intelligence 11, Wisdom 13, Charisma 13). It has hearing and normal vision out to a range of 120 feet. It communicates by transmitting emotion to the creature carrying or wielding it.</p>\n<p>The sword&rsquo;s purpose is to fight evil. The sword has the following additional properties:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The sword continually sheds bright light in a 15-foot radius and dim light for an additional 15 feet. Only by destroying the sword can this light be extinguished.</li>\n<li>A lawful good creature can attune itself to the sword in 1 minute.</li>\n<li>While attuned to the weapon, the sword&rsquo;s wielder can use the sword to cast the @Item[sqKljy1gEB7T41Hi]{Crusader's Mantle} spell. Once used, this property of the sword can&rsquo;t be used again until the next dawn.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>FoundryVTT:&nbsp;</strong>The daily spell is not automated.&nbsp; It might be added as a once daily spell ability to the base character and deleted if the sword is <em>lost.</em></p>",
      "chat": "<p>Proficiency with a shortsword allows you to add your proficiency bonus to the attack roll for any attack you make with it.</p>",
      "unidentified": "Shortsword"
    },
